{
  "answer": "**The *Parāśara Smṛti*, Chapter 1, contains the warning in verses Par_1.45–46:**\n\n> The one from whose house an *atithi* turns away with his hopes shattered—his ancestors will not eat his offerings for fifteen years.[^1]  \n> For him from whose house an *atithi* turns away with hopes shattered, his fire offering is as useless as a thousand loads of wood and a hundred pots of clarified butter.[^2]\n\nThese verses emphasize the grave consequences for a householder who fails to honor a guest (*atithi*), who arrives during the *Vaiśvadeva* ritual.\n\n[^1]: *Parāśara Smṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/01/translation/#p-d461ee).  \n[^2]: *Parāśara Smṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/01/translation/#p-51e1c4).",
